	<madsrdf:citationSource>Wikipedia, August 9, 2021</madsrdf:citationSource>
	<madsrdf:citationNote>(under Galápagos Islands: the islands are known for their large number of endemic species that were studied by Charles Darwin during the second voyage of HMS Beagle. His observations and collections contributed to the inception of Darwin's theory of evolution by means of natural selection)</madsrdf:citationNote>
